@node COSAFRONTRAY3 "What is FrontRay3"


                          @{b}What is FrontRay3 @{ub}

 FrontRay3 is a graphic interface to the CLI commands of the famous raytracer PD POVRay 3.0.
 You can find more info on POVRay in the POVRay's package self .


@endnode

@node COSAPOVRAY "What is POVRay"


                          @{b}What is POVRay@{ub}

 POVRay 3.0 is a public domain raytracer and is considered one of the best software 3D as
 quality of rendering.
 With a text editor , you may to write the entire scene 3D as if you are programming.
 When you have wrote the scene, run POVRay with the file scene as parameter.

 POVRay is frequently updated and there's for many hardware platform.


 You can find @{b}POVRay 3.0@{ub} at: http://www.povray.org/
 POVRay 3.0 unufficial for Amiga  is been ported by @{"Joshua Marshall" link RINGRAZIAMENTI}
 (thank you very much Josh) and can find it in Aminet:   @{i}aminet/gfx/3D/pov3c.lha @{ui}

@endnode


@node INSTALLAZIONE "Installation"

                          @{b}Installation@{ub}


 The installation in your hard-drive is very simple, copy all file of the archive where do
 you like.

 The archive contains the following files:

  +FrontRay3/                        MAIN DIRECTORY
   FrontRay3.info                           icon file
        FrontRay3                    Main program
        FrontRay3.info                      main program's icon
        FrontRay3_I.guide            AmigaGuide info in italian language
        FrontRay3_I.guide.info              icon file
        FrontRay3_E.guide            AmigaGuide info in english language
        FrontRay3_E.guide.info              icon file
        +Catalogs/                   Drawer catalogs
         Catalogs.info                      icon file
             +italiano/              Drawer of italian catalog
              italiano.info                 icon file
                  /frontray3.catalog Italian catalog
        +ct/                         Drawer whit catalog translation
         ct.info                            icon file
            translation.readme       Readme for .ct file
            translation.readme.info         icon file
            frontray3.ct              Catalog translation
            frontray3.ct.info                icon file


@endnode


@node PROGRAMMIUSATI "Programs used"


                          @{b}Programs used@{ub}


 It use the @{b}Magic User Interface (MUI) @{ub} by Stefan Stuntz ( you can find it
 with other Sasg products at the beautiful site @{i}http://www.sasg.com/@{ui}).

 Compiled with @{b}Amiga-E  v3.2e @{ub} by  Wouter  van  Oortmerssen
 ( Home page at: @{i}http://mars.let.uva.nl/wouter/@{ui}  )

 Editor used @{b}GoldED 4.x @{ub}by Dietmar Eilert
 ( Home page @{i}http://www.clearlight.com/~dietmar@{ui} )


@endnode

@node COSARICHIEDE "System requirements"


                          @{b}System requirements @{ub}


    Software min.: OS >= 2.1  e  MUI >= 3.x
    Hardware min.: Amiga with 68000 and 1Mb RAM



@endnode

@node COSADINUOVO "What's new"


                          @{b}What's new @{ub}


    New features from FrontRay to FrontRay3:


    @{"File I/O" link FILEIO}
    @{"Rendering" link RENDERING}
    @{"Animation" link ANIMATION}  NEW!
    @{"Display" link DISPLAY}
    @{"Comand" link COMANDI}    NEW!
    @{"Various" link VARIE}

    @{"What don't support" link COSANONSUPPORTA}


@endnode


@node FILEIO "File I/O"


                          Section @{b}File I/O @{ub}


   - New formats output ( TARGA compr./noncompr. , PNG , Unix PPM )

   - Depth, bit by color from 5 to 16 in PNG format

   - Transparence Alpha ( PNG and TARGA )

@endnode

@node RENDERING "Rendering"


                          Section @{b}Rendering @{ub}


   - Adaptive super-samplin method switch for Antialias

   - Radiosity

   - Remove bounds

   - Split Unions

   - Light and vista buffers



@endnode

@node ANIMATION "Animation"


                          @{b}Animation @{ub}@{u}( New section ) @{uu}

   The "custom" animation of FrontRay have been eliminated.
   Now is POVRay that handle animation internaly.
   Add these new section:

   - Initial and final value of Clock

   - Initial and final animation frame

   - Initial and final animation sub-frame

   - Cyclic Animation ( a frame equal to the first frame is added)

   - Field rendering, switch odd and even field flag on/off

   - Field rendering, only switch odd field on/off


@endnode

@node DISPLAY "Display"


                          Section@{b}Display @{ub}


   - Output video only for Cybergfx ( due to the porting ), if you haven't a Cybergfx
     driver the option will don't have effect, however , the output will be redirect
     on file.

   - Start and end size for Mosaic preview. The values must to be
     power of 2: 1 - 2 - 4 - 8....


@endnode

@node COMANDI "Command"


                          Section@{b}Command @{ub}@{u}( New Section ) @{uu}


   - In these new section you may to select same commands to execute at one specific event,
     and what POVRay have to make when the command fail.
     I.e. you want to save your output files in a zip farchive using lha, you have to select
     the command LHA with the asl requester and the relative argument from the pop-up list;
     then select what to do if LHA failed.



@endnode

@node VARIE "Various"


                          Section @{b}Various @{ub}


   - Compatibility with 1.0, 2.0 and 3.0 POVRay's version

   - Creation of a file .INI ( in these file there are all, active and not, parameters
     of POVRay). These is useful in the case you deal the scene and would like also other
     people see the image as well as you have saw.




@endnode

@node COSANONSUPPORTA "What don't support"


                          @{b}What don't support: @{ub}


   - The output on either console or file of various output message ( that are on console
     by default).




@endnode

@node STORIADIFRONTRAY "Frontray's history"


                          @{b}Frontray's history: @{ub}

            @{b}FrontRay3 1.2 @{ub} 29 May 1997 :

                       - Minimal improvment to the interface

            @{b}FrontRay3 1.1 @{ub} 17 May 1997 :

                       - Now it run on OS2.1
                       - Minimal improvment to the interface

            @{i}FrontRay3 1.0 @{ui}April 1997 : ****  It support POVRay 3.0 *****

                       - Now it support almost the parameters of POVRay 3.0

            @{i}FrontRay  1.0 @{ui}September 1996 : It support POVRay 2.2

                       - The very first version of FrontRay






@endnode

